Question 11: How does the rating relate to the level of discount?

Let’s observe trends:

•	Higher discounts (50%+) do not always correlate with higher ratings.

•	Some products with lower discounts (30–40%) had higher ratings like 4.6.

•	Many top-rated products are in the 40–45% discount range.

✅ Insight:

There’s no strong correlation between high discounts and high ratings. Quality or brand perception seems to drive ratings more than discount.

